CLOSEPhoenix-based Banner Health, Arizona's largest health system, is offering some employees voluntary, unpaid sabbaticals, officials confirmed Thursday.
(Photo: Mark Henle/The Republic)Phoenix-based Banner Health, Arizona's largest health system, is offering some employees voluntary, unpaid sabbaticals, officials confirmed Thursday.
Doug Ducey last month ordered hospitals to halt elective surgeries, which has significantly reduced workloads for some health care workers.
"There are certainly some individuals in the health care industry, Banner Health included, who have a lot of work to do right now.
Health care workers who staff outpatient clinics and surgery centers, for example, would have significantly less work than usual.